        <bioghist id="ref7">
            <head>Biographical Note</head>
            <p>Maude White Hardie was a writer and poet who lived with her husband, Charles Hardie, on East 19th Street in Brooklyn, N.Y. Charles Hardie was a chemist who worked for a German Aniline Company that later became the well-known I.G. Farben Industry.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref2">
            <head>Scope and Contents</head>
            <p>This collection contains the papers of Brooklyn writer and poet Maude White Hardie, including autobiographical writings, poems, essays, correspondence and family letters, diaries, books, postcards, brochures, and legal and financial documents.</p>
        </scopecontent>
